&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>The Sanskrit word Prakriti or Prakruti has multiple meanings and is used in the Bhagavad Gita in different contexts. In the English language, we try to translate it to &amp;ldquo;Nature&amp;rdquo;. But, does this word really summarize the meaning of the Sanskrit word? To better understand, you need to look at these 25 slokas. You may not get a complete answer, but it will help you delve deeper and transcend existence.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>